ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2, Daily

ElementDescription: Initial rating of pain after deep breathing, on 0 to 10 numeric rating scale with 0.5 increments; as part of functional testing for deep breathing and coughing
Final rating of pain after deep breathing, on 0 to 10 numeric rating scale with 0.5 increments; as part of functional testing for deep breathing and coughing
Final rating of pain after coughing, on 0 to 10 numeric rating scale with 0.5 increments; as part of functional testing for deep breathing and coughing
Indicator of completion of the functional testing for deep breathing and coughing
If functional testing for deep breathing and coughing not complete, what portion was completed
Notes: 1= Did not attempt either deep breathing or coughing tasks; 2= Did not complete deep breathing portion only;  3= Did not complete coughing portion only

ElementDescription: Free text of additional notes; as part of functional testing for deep breathing and coughing
